<subSubSection id="A1D565563F1EFF8EFF26FEE2FE30FE68" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1EFF89FF26FEE2FB96FDEF" blockId="43.[151,1437,320,707]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Morphology. D VI + I,7; A I,6–7; P 16–17 (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F1EFF89FD47FEE2FC71FE9E" author="Kovacic, M. &amp; Ordines, F. &amp; Schliewen, U." box="[678,913,356,383]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="447 - 460" refId="ref59146" refString="Kovacic, M., Ordines, F. &amp; Schliewen, U. (2017 a) A new species of Buenia (Teleostei: Gobiidae) from the western Mediterranean Sea, with the description of this genus. Zootaxa, 4050 (5), 447 - 460. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4250.5.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kovačić 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FCEAFEE3FCDCFE9F" box="[779,828,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">et al</emphasis>
. 2017a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F1EFF89FC7AFEE2FB9EFE9E" author="Ordines, F. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Vivas, M. &amp; Garcia-Ruiz, C. &amp; Guijarro, B." box="[923,1150,356,383]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="275 - 282" refId="ref62095" refString="Ordines, F., Kovacic, M., Vivas, M., Garcia-Ruiz, C. &amp; Guijarro, B. (2019 a) Westernmost Mediterranean records of three gobiid species (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae). Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 49, 275 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIEP / 02604" type="journal article" year="2019">
Ordines 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FC1BFEE3FBCAFE9F" box="[1018,1066,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">et al</emphasis>
. 2019a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F1EFF89FB69FEE2FB34FE9E" author="Ordines, F. &amp; Ramirez-Amaro, S. &amp; Burgos C. &amp; Baro, J. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Sobrino, I." box="[1160,1236,356,383]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="85 - 89" refId="ref62161" refString="Ordines, F., Ramirez-Amaro, S. Burgos C., Baro, J., Kovacic, M. &amp; Sobrino, I. (2019 b) First record of Buenia massutii Kovacic, Ordines, &amp; Schliewen, 2017 in the Atlantic Ocean based on molecular and morphological evidences. Journal of Applied Ichthyology, 36, 85 - 89. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jai. 13985" type="journal article" year="2019">2019b</bibRefCitation>
). Small goby with subcylindrical body, laterally compressed towards caudal fin. Head slightly depressed and fairly long. Eyes large and close together, with narrow interorbital space. Caudal peduncle slender, clearly lower than body height. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FAA6FE2AFED1FDEE" bold="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Second spine of first dorsal fin elongate in males, reaching to or behind posterior end of the second dorsal fin when folded down.</emphasis>
Caudal fin rounded. Scales present, visibility on live specimens unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1EFF89FF26FD9EFEF1FD22" blockId="43.[151,1437,320,707]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Freshly dead coloration. Head and body yellowish white to dusky white with scattered yellow, orange and dark brown markings. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FE74FDBBFC74FD7E" bold="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
Body with 5 black marks, the first one over abdomen below first dorsal fin, three short vertical black marks at and below lateral midline and fifth longer vertical mark on caudal-fin base (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F1EFF89FACCFDE6FA6FFD9B" box="[1325,1423,608,634]" captionStart="FIGURE 49" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1953,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,730,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-221@43.[151,1436,730,1929]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 49. A) Freshly dead coloration of Buenia massutii, photo by M. Kovačić, Mallorca, Balearic Islands, Spain. B) Buenia cf. massutii live coloration in its natural habitat, photo by X. Rufray, Saint-Raphaël, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601721/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 49a</figureCitation>
). Eyes grayish to brownish, occasionally with small pale gray dots.
</emphasis>
A rectangular area of small close-set dark dots below eye.
</paragraph>
<caption id="BDB066553F1EFF89FF76F827FB7DF83C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601721" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6601721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601721/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" startId="43.[151,250,1953,1977]" targetBox="[151,1436,730,1929]" targetPageId="43">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F1EFF89FF76F827FB7DF83C" blockId="43.[151,1436,1953,2014]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FF76F827FEFFF858" bold="true" box="[151,287,1953,1977]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">FIGURE 49.</emphasis>
A) Freshly dead coloration of 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FDB1F824FD18F858" box="[592,760,1954,1977]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F1EFF89FDB1F824FD14F858" authorityName="Kovacic, Ordines &amp; Schliewen" authorityYear="2017" box="[592,756,1954,1977]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Buenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="massutii">Buenia massutii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
photo by M. Kovačić, Mallorca, Balearic Islands, Spain. B) 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F1EFF89FAB5F824FEECF83C" authorityName="Kovacic, Ordines &amp; Schliewen" authorityYear="2017" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Buenia" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="massutii">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FAB5F824FA7CF858" box="[1364,1436,1954,1977]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Buenia</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F1EFF89FF59F840FEECF83C" box="[184,268,1990,2013]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">massutii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
live coloration in its natural habitat, photo by X. Rufray, Saint-Raphaël, Southern France.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F19FF8EFF26FF11FDC3FF50" blockId="44.[151,1437,151,393]" box="[199,547,151,177]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F19FF8EFE9EFF11FDFCFF50" authorityName="Iljin" authorityYear="1930" box="[383,540,151,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Buenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="affinis">
